# Cursor rules for Baby Pulmo

You are working on Baby Pulmo, a Next.js 14 healthcare app — WhatsApp-native AI for pediatric pneumonia screening in rural Bangladesh.

## Non-negotiable rule

**Never propose adding a runtime LLM call in the caregiver-facing path** (webhook → classifier → reply). Severity decisions are deterministic in `lib/claude.ts::decideSeverityMultiModal`. Bangla audio is served from the clinician-vetted stock library in `lib/tts.ts::STOCK_BANGLA`. This is the BMRC ethics review claim.

See `ARCHITECTURE.md` §3 for the carve-out describing where LLMs ARE allowed: build-time, one-shot ingest, CHW-side investigation, partner MCP, federated learning, CXR vision (DenseNet121, not an LLM).

## Style

- TypeScript strict mode. No `any`.
- Tailwind for styling. No other CSS systems.
- Prefer existing helpers in `lib/` over re-implementing.
- Use `process.env.*` per `.env.example`. Don't introduce new env vars without updating `.env.example`.
- Imports: relative for same-directory, absolute (`@/`) for cross-directory.

## File-path discipline

Every claim cites a file path. Before adding a TODO or claim "we have X", grep to confirm.

## Read for context

- `CLAUDE.md` — canonical project context.
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` — 8-layer system + §3 LLM carve-out.
- `memory-bank/` — Cline Memory Bank (6 files).
